#### System information

Geth version: `1.9.14`
OS & Version: Ubuntu

#### Expected behaviour
To remain in sync with the network

#### Actual behaviour
Geth seems to halt syncing or is busy doing something else at sporadic times.  Running on AWS i3.xlarge and has been a up and running for over one year. 


#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour
Docker
```
FROM ethereum/client-go:v1.9.14
ENTRYPOINT ["geth", "--syncmode=fast", "--ipcdisable", "--verbosity=3", "--maxpeers=50", "--cache=8192", "--rpc", "--rpcapi=eth,debug,web3,net,admin", "--rpcvhosts=*", "--rpccorsdomain=*", "--rpcaddr=0.0.0.0", "--ws", "--wsaddr=0.0.0.0", "--wsapi=eth,debug,web3,pubsub,admin,net", "--wsorigins=*"]
```

